Final Year Project

Bio-Inspired ROV
Thruster System

Individual Project ¬∑ First Class ¬∑ IEEE Publication In Progress

Design of a Bio-Inspired Thruster
for Remotely Operated Vehicles

Coventry University ¬∑ Singapore Dec 2024 ‚Äì Mar 2025 Solo Project ‚Äî Pool Tested 7 Engineering Disciplines
Pool Test ‚Äî Live Demonstration
Full Prototype ¬∑ Poolside
3D CAD ¬∑ SolidWorks Design

A fully self-designed, fabricated, coded, and pool-tested underwater propulsion system inspired by seahorse locomotion. The system integrates a crank-rocker mechanism driving four waterproof servos to generate sinusoidal fin oscillation ‚Äî producing organised vortex structures and measurable thrust. Validated through ANSYS FEA, ANSYS Fluent CFD, embedded Arduino control, FMEA reliability analysis, and physical pool testing ‚Äî all within a single final year project.
